</taxonomicName>
’ refers to the robust style in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,780,1218]" box="[197,1110,967,994]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,967,993]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description.</emphasis>
Body length (including tegmen): 
<number box="[747,769,967,993]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="3.0">3</number>
, 5.0 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[820,835,967,993]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">–</emphasis>
<quantity box="[835,920,968,994]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1mm</quantity>
, Ƥ, 
<quantity box="[968,1106,967,994]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="5.75" valueMax="5.9" valueMin="5.6">
5.6 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1005,1020,967,993]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">–</emphasis>
5.9mm
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,780,1218]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Male genitalia: Pygophore elongate, dorsal margin strongly sinuate in lateral aspect. Style relatively broad with strong apical process. Connective stem about 
<number box="[819,856,1042,1068]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times longer than arms. Aedeagal shaft distinctly broader at midlength in lateral view, apical process with length approximately 
<number box="[1071,1084,1080,1106]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1094,1109,1080,1106]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="4.0">4</number>
length of shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,780,1218]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,327,1117,1143]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished by the sinuate dorsal margin of the pygophore and robust style.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
